    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a museum-quality 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, a masterclass in lightweight engineering and rotational physics. This specimen features the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, exhibiting optimal compression across all rotor faces. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise 5-speed manual transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring surgical torque delivery. Every suspension bushing and the factory-spec double-wishbone geometry remain in concours condition, providing the tactile feedback and 50/50 weight distribution this chassis is famed for. With zero aftermarket modifications, original vacuum line routing, and a pristine cooling system, this FD represents the pinnacle of preserved 90s JDM performance.",
